  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (fidelity gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: the CFD model employs a simplified laminar-flow assumption and omits turbulent stress contributions to the scalar hemolysis transport equation; this simplification is noted in the model description but no validation activity tests the sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to that exclusion.",
