      "rationale": "Model employs incompressible Navier-Stokes equations with steady multiple reference frame (MRF) rotation treatment. Blood modeled as Newtonian fluid. Hemolysis predicted via power-law scalar damage accumulation (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation). Model description explicitly states that turbulence modeling is omitted and a simplified laminar-flow assumption is applied throughout; no sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study is documented to quantify the impact of this exclusion on hemolysis predictions at the higher rotational speeds where transitional flow is physically present."
