    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Validation results demonstrate quantitative agreement with FDA bench data across all 5 operating points. The model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The laminar-flow simplification is noted in the model form factor; the assessment team concluded that agreement in mean velocity and pressure-head QoIs provides sufficient confidence, and that turbulence effects are secondary at the operating conditions tested.",
